website_summaries.verdict: High-quality formula includes nutritious ingredients, such as blueberries and spinach, alongside a huge portion of raw fish-based protein.
pros: Whitefish and salmon are the first two ingredients
Works as either a complete dehydrated meal or food topper
cons: It's only available in a 2-pound bag

customer_reviews.title: Delicious and nutritious!
customer_reviews.text: I use this as a treat for my agility dogs and they love it (even my super picky pup)!! I love the fact that it is moist, the pieces are small enough for my border collies to easily eat (no need to break apart), they're healthy, and!! NO poultry!! This is our go-to treat. As an extra bonus, the price compared to a normal bag of treats is fantastic!! (Think about the fact that even if you're buying a 1 pound bag of "zukes" you're probably paying at least $15 ($30 for 2 pounds) - but probably more. And this is better quality!)
customer_reviews.author: JKo

customer_reviews.title: Awesome training treat!
customer_reviews.text: Use this product for training treats in agility. Suddenly I am the most popular human for all the dogs in the class! They are nice and moist and do not take a lot of time for the dog to chew like larger crunchier treats. Bought a smaller air proof container to keep them moist in my training bag. Also need to remember to remove leftovers from my treat bag because they dry out.
customer_reviews.author: Esined

customer_reviews.title: My dog seems to like it
customer_reviews.text: I usually buy different kinds of freeze dried raw food for his breakfast. I saw this air-dried food and decided to try. He has been eating it for the past 2 weeks. I am glad he likes it as he is a picky eater.
customer_reviews.author: h a

customer_reviews.title: My older dog loves it
customer_reviews.text: I have an older small dog that has been getting more finicky by the day. I suspect she’s having trouble with her teeth and no longer interested in chewing dry kibble. She seems to love the flavor and not have any trouble chewing this food.
customer_reviews.author: Kristi C.

customer_reviews.title: Check expiration before you feed to your pet!!!
customer_reviews.text: I received this package on 3/16/18 product says best used by 30NOV17. The worst part is I fed to my dog before I realized, thankfully she only had a small bite from her bowl before I threw her expired dinner away. It was easy to take away from her she didn't even seem too interested, maybe she could taste the staleness. This product has RAW foods the quality control of this product in storage/warehouse needs to be more closely monitored.
customer_reviews.author: Leila

customer_reviews.title: This kibble is excellent. Unfortunately only one of my dogs likes the ...
customer_reviews.text: This kibble is excellent. Unfortunately only one of my dogs likes the fish flavor. It smells quite strong so you can't fool the dog by mixing it with other foods. From now on I'll stick to the chicken flavor that both my dogs love. If your dog likes fish it's a great variety.
customer_reviews.author: Raquel D.

customer_reviews.title: Satiated Shih Tzu
customer_reviews.text: This food as a morning 1/4 cup topper has really helped my Shih Tzu remain satiated all day. Her standing in the kitchen groaning as if she were dying for more food days are gone.
customer_reviews.author: SANDRA

customer_reviews.title: Dogs like this food
customer_reviews.text: Pretty spendy for a 2lb bag. Dogs seem to like it, and they are sensitive to new foods and at 7 and 13 years old they are doing well with this food.

customer_reviews.title: Great training treat, but too expensive for mealtime feeding.
customer_reviews.text: Picked up a bag when I first saw this at Petco... paid full price, but had to try it! I needed a smelly, tasty, high protein training treat my dog would love while out walking. This filled the bill. Too expensive to use at mealtime, though. Now that I see it on Amazon, that's where I'll buy when we need more. Hopefully, the price will go down by then!

product_meta.title: Wellness Core Air Dried Grain Free Natural Dry Dog Food, 2-Pound Bag
product_meta.description: Flavor Name:Whitefish & SalmonWellness CORE Air Dried Natural Grain Free Dry Dog Food is healthy, grain free dog food for adult dogs featuring tender protein morsels made with 70% natural, raw protein fortified with vitamins and minerals for whole body health and then air dried for the taste of raw and the ease and convenience of kibble, yet no refrigeration required. Wellness CORE grain free dog food formulas are based on the nutritional philosophy that dogs thrive on a diet mainly comprised of meat. Each grain free, nutrient-rich formula provides high quality protein for your dog.

Poultry Free Dry Dog Food Features 70-Percent Whitefish And Salmon Recipes, Great For Dogs With Protein Sensitivity
Protein Rich, Grain Free Dog Food With The Taste Of Raw And The Ease Of Kibble, Yet No Refrigeration Required
Dry Dog Food To Be Served As A Complete, Balanced Meal Or Add On Top For An Extra Boost Of Protein
Healthy Dry Dog Food With No Wheat, Corn, Soy Or Artificial Flavors, Colors Or Preservatives
